whereas.text:
Whereas the Vietnam War was fought in Vietnam from 1961 to
			 1975, and involved North Vietnam and the Viet Cong in conflict with the United
			 States Armed Forces and South Vietnam;

Whereas by the end of 1965, there were 80,000 United
			 States troops in Vietnam, and by 1969 a peak of approximately 543,000 troops
			 was reached;

Whereas more than 58,000 members of the United States
			 Armed Forces lost their lives in Vietnam and more than 300,000 members of the
			 Armed Forces were wounded;
